  1→//! `sandbox_packages` tool — lists packages pre-installed in the sandbox
  2→//! container, grouped by category.
  3→//!
  4→//! The LLM calls this tool before running commands that need specific tools
  5→//! (image processing, audio/video, document conversion, GIS, etc.) to check
  6→//! what's available, instead of bloating every system prompt with the full
  7→//! package list.
  8→//!
  9→//! **Hybrid mode**: the tool always returns the configured package list
 10→//! (categorized).  When a sandbox container is already running for the
 11→//! current session it also queries `dpkg-query` inside the container and
 12→//! reports any extra packages that were installed at runtime.
 13→
 14→use std::{collections::HashSet, sync::Arc};
 15→
 16→use {
 17→    async_trait::async_trait,
 18→    serde_json::{Value, json},
 19→    tracing::debug,
 20→};
 21→
 22→#[cfg(feature = "metrics")]
 23→use moltis_metrics::{counter, histogram};
 24→
 25→use moltis_agents::tool_registry::AgentTool;
 26→
 27→use crate::{exec::ExecOpts, sandbox::SandboxRouter};
 28→
